| `MoneyValue`, `CurrencyConversionTable`, `CurrencyConverter` | `rate()` returned `1` on both branches |
| 3 `*RoundingPolicy` classes + resolver | all three bodies computed `Math.round(v*100)/100` |
| 3 `*DiscountStrategy` classes + registry + factory | fixed order, three multipliers, never extended |
| `PipelineStage`/`PricingPipeline`/`PricingPipelineFactory` | exactly 4 stages, always the same 4 |

Two caveats on the winner, both behaviour-preserving but worth your eye:

- The `"rounding"` currency guard is now a membership check against `SUPPORTED_CURRENCIES` rather than a resolver throw. Same message, same trigger — but the `Currency` type already excludes anything else, so it only fires on unchecked casts.
